  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As of now, `go-ethereum`'s `rpc.Client` does not in any way expose the underlying `websocket.Conn`. This makes creating methods for connection keep-alive difficult (as sending `ping` is not possible).\r\n\r\nI am wondering if there can be any support for either:\r\n- Automatic pings (or even manual `Ping` functions).\r\n- Exposing the underlying `websocket.Conn`.\r\n\r\nI acknowledge that the Client does have built-in support for automatic retry, however this is still very cumbersome in the case of using `eth-subscribe`. We've had experience with Infura's websocket server which often closes connections even with active subscriptions (sometimes as often as 1.5 minute!) \r\nRight now our workaround is to proxy the websocket connection and inject pings in the middle, which is far from optimal.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: v1.9.14\r\n\r\n",
